    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Pages H2349-H2350]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. GRAVES of Louisiana:H.R. 1679.[[Page H2350]]Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article 1, Section 8 of the United States Constitution</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    <title>FEMA Accountability, Modernization and Transparency Act of 2017</title>
    <congress>115</congress>
    <createDate>2017-03-23T05:20:05Z</createDate>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2017-03-22</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-05-31T21:15:06Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2017-03-22T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>FEMA Accountability, Modernization and Transparency Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to ensure that the ongoing modernization of the grant systems for the administration of assistance under the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act includes:</p> <ul> <li>an online interface for applicants to complete application forms, submit materials, and access the status of applications;</li> <li>mechanisms to eliminate duplication of benefits; and</li> <li>a means of sharing information among agencies and with state, local, and tribal governments to eliminate the need to file multiple applications and speed disaster recovery.</li> </ul> <p>FEMA shall deliver the system capabilities in increments or iterations as working components for applicant use. </p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2017-05-02</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-05-31T21:15:26Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2017-05-02T18:16:27Z</updateDate>
          <actionDesc>Passed House without amendment</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</p> <p><strong>FEMA Accountability, Modernization and Transparency Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to ensure that the ongoing modernization of the grant systems for the administration of assistance under the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act includes:</p> <ul> <li>an online interface for applicants to complete application forms, submit materials, and access the status of applications;</li> <li>mechanisms to eliminate duplication of benefits; and</li> <li>a means of sharing information among agencies and with state, local, and tribal governments to eliminate the need to file multiple applications and speed disaster recovery.</li> </ul> <p>FEMA shall deliver the system capabilities in increments or iterations as working components for applicant use. </p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>81</versionCode>
          <name>Passed House without amendment</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
